Package: geodetect
Type: Package
Title: Geospatial Object Detection Using Deep Learning
Version: 0.2.0
Date: 2025-04-27
Authors@R: 
    person("geodetect", "Authors", email = "lalitiaas@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Provides a complete workflow for deep learning-based object detection
    on geospatial raster data (satellite imagery, aerial photographs, drone imagery).
    Implements Faster R-CNN with a ResNet-50 + FPN backbone via the 'torch' package —
    no Python installation required. Handles the full pipeline: reading
    geospatially-referenced rasters with 'terra', tiling into overlapping chips,
    assembling annotated datasets from bounding-box labels stored as 'sf' vector
    objects, training detection models, running sliding-window inference on large
    rasters, back-projecting detected bounding boxes to geographic coordinates, and
    exporting results as 'sf' objects for downstream GIS analysis.
